014 FIFA World Cup]]\n|-\n| 2 || 13 June 2015 || [[T\u00f3rsv\u00f8llur]], [[T\u00f3rshavn]], Faroe Islands || {{fb|FRO}} ||align=center| '''1'''\u20132 ||align=center| [[2015 Faroe Islands v Greece football match|1\u20132]] || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying]]\n|-\n| 3 || 9 November 2017 || [[Stadion Maksimir]], [[Zagreb]], Croatia || {{fb|CRO}} ||align=center| '''1'''\u20132 ||align=center| 1\u20134 || [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Milan'''\n*[[Serie A]]: [[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311]]{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n'''Borussia Dortmund'''\n*[[DFB-Pokal]]: [[2016\u201317 DFB-Pokal|2016\u201317]]{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n*[[DFL-Supercup]]: [[2013 DFL-Supercup|2013]], [[2014 DFL-Supercup|2014]]{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n'''Arsenal'''\n*[[UEFA Europa League]] runner-up: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Europa League|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48368406 |title=Chelsea 4\u20131 Arsenal |first=Chris |last=Bevan |work=BBC Sport |date=29 May 2019 |accessdate=29 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Greek football PSAP awards#Superleague Greece Awards|Best Greek Young Player]]: [[2007\u201308 Superleague Greece|2007\u201308]]{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{FIFA player}}\n*{{UEFA player}}\n*[https://www.premierleague.com/players/5093/Sokratis/overview  Overview] \u2013 [[Premier League]]\n*{{Cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/clubs/borussia-dortmund/kader/ |title=Bundesliga profile |access-date=18 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715011824/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/clubs/borussia-dortmund/kader/ |archive-date=15 July 2018 |url-status=dead  }}\n*{{ESPN FC}}\n*{{Soccerway}}\n\n{{Arsenal F.C. squad}}\n{{Super League Greece young footballer of the year}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Greece squads\n| bg = #0000cd\n| fg = #FFFFFF\n| list1 = \n{{Greece squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Greece squad UEFA Euro 2012}}\n{{Greece squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Papastathopoulos, Sokratis}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Kalamata]]\n[[Category:Greek footballers]]\n[[Category:Greece youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Greece under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Greece international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:AEK Athens F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Niki Volou FC players]]\n[[Category:Genoa C.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:A.C. Milan players]]\n[[Category:SV Werder Bremen players]]\n[[Category:Borussia Dortmund players]]\n[[Category:Arsenal F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2012 players]]\n[[Category:2014 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate sportspeople in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Sokratis Papastathopoulos\n| image = 1 Sokratis Papastathopoulos.jpg\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Sokratis playing for [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in 2018\n| fullname = Sokratis Papastathopoulos<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/1335777 |title=2019/20 Premier League squads confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=3 September 2019 |accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|6|9|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/86377/sokratis-papastathopoulos |title=Sokratis Papastathopoulos |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Kalamata]], [[Peloponnese]], Greece\n| height = 1.86 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/5093/Sokratis/overview |title=Sokratis: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]\n| clubnumber = 5\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = Aiantas Kalamatas\n| youthclubs2 = Apollon Petalidiou\n| youthyears2 = \u20132004\n| youthclubs3 = [[AEK F.C. Academy|AEK Athens]]\n| youthyears3 = 2004\u20132005\n| years1 = 2005\u20132008\n| clubs1 = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n| caps1 = 42\n| goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2006\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Niki Volos F.C.|Niki Volou]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 11\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs3 = [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]]\n| caps3 = 51\n| goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2010\u20132012\n| clubs4 = [[A.C. Milan|Milan]]\n| caps4 = 5\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs5 = \u2192 [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] (loan)\n| caps5 = 30\n| goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs6 = [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]]\n| caps6 = 29\n| goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2013\u20132018\n| clubs7 = [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n| caps7 = 130\n| goals7 = 7\n| years8 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs8 = [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]\n| caps8 = 44\n| goals8 = 3\n| nationalyears1 = 2003\u20132005\n| nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-17 football team|Greece U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 11\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalyears2 = 2005\u20132007\n| nationalteam2 = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 13\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2007\u20132010\n| nationalteam3 = [[Greece national under-21 football team|Greece U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 7\n| nationalgoals3 = 2\n| nationalyears4 = 2008\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Greece national football team|Greece]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 90\n| nationalgoals4 = 3\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Team|{{fb|Greece}}}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[UEFA European Under-19 Championship|European U19 Championship]]|[[2007 UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship|2007]]}}\n| club-update = 18:45, 7 March 2020 (UTC).\n| nationalteam-update = 21:45, 8 September 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Sokratis Papastathopoulos''' ({{lang-el|\u03a3\u03c9\u03ba\u03c1\u03ac\u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2}}, {{IPA-el|so\u02c8kratis papasta\u02c8\u03b8opulos|pron}}; born 9 June 1988), commonly known [[:wikt:mononym|mononym]]ously as '''Sokratis''',<ref>{{cite news |title=Sokratis o Papastathopoulos? Questo \u00e8 il dilemma |url=http://www.milannews.it/?action=read&idnotizia=31205 |first=Francesco |last=Somma |website=milannews.it |date=3 August 2010 |accessdate=12 August 2010 |language=Italian}}</ref> is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre back]] for English {{English football updater|Arsenal}} club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and the [[Greece national football team|Greece national team]].\n\n==Club career==\n===AEK Athens===\nPapastathopoulos joined AEK Athens from <!--Red link [[Apollon Petalidiou]]-->Apollon Petalidiou after being scouted by [[Toni Savevski]]. On 26 October 2005, he made his debut for AEK in a [[Greek Football Cup|Greek Cup]] match against [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]], scoring in the seventh minute of the game to help lead AEK to a 3\u20130 win.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n\n====Niki Volou (loan)====\nIn January 2006, he was loaned to [[Second Division (Greece)|Greek Second Division]] club [[Niki Volos F.C.|Niki Volou]] for six months to gain first-team football and gather valuable experience. He made a total of 15 appearances for Niki Volou.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n\n====AEK Athens return====\nDuring the [[2006-07 Superleague Greece]], Papastathopoulos managed to make 14 appearances whilst competing against the likes of [[Bruno Cirillo]], [[Traianos Dellas]] and [[Vangelis Moras]]. In AEK Athens' [[2006\u201307 UEFA Champions League]] campaign, Papastathopoulos managed to play in three out of six group games. In these three games, AEK managed one win (the famous 1\u20130 victory over [[A.C. Milan|Milan]], where he man-marked [[Filippo Inzaghi]]), one draw (the 2\u20132 away draw with [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]]) and one loss (the 3\u20131 away defeat to [[Lille OSC|Lille]]). During the [[2007\u201308 Superleague Greece]], he was a mainstay in AEK's defence, keeping out competition from [[Geraldo Alves (footballer, born 1980)|Geraldo Alves]]. He also played in the [[2007\u201308 UEFA Champions League|2007\u201308 Champions League]] campaign, and in a Superleague match, he became AEK's youngest-ever captain, at age 19, in a game against local [[Athens]] rivals [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] in 2008.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n\n===Genoa===\nOn 1 August 2008, Papastathopoulos agreed to transfer to [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]] of the Italian [[Serie A]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aekfc.gr/index.asp?a_id=74&n_id=4314|script-title=el:\u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03ba\u03bf\u03af\u03bd\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7|trans-title=Communication|date= 1 August 2008|accessdate=11 June 2011|publisher=AEK Athens F.C. |language=Greek|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080805100628/http://www.aekfc.gr/index.asp?a_id=74&n_id=4314|archivedate=5 August 2008}}</ref> He also played a club friendly against Genoa on the same day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.genoacfc.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=5291&Itemid=31|title=IL GENOA DA' LEZIONE DI GRECO|date=1 August 2010|accessdate=11 June 2011|publisher=Genoa C.F.C. |language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nHe made his debut for Genoa on 27 September 2008 against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]], followed by a start against [[Ravenna Calcio|Ravenna]] in the [[Coppa Italia]] a few days later. His first goal for Genoa came on 5 October 2008 at home against [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]]. Genoa won the game 3\u20132, but Papastathopoulos was sent off in the 89th minute<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/soccer/report?gameId=251286|title=Genoa vs. Napoli \u2013 Football Match Report \u2013 October 5, 2008 |website=ESPN FC |accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=251286&&cc=5739 | title = Genoa 3\u20132 Napoli |website=ESPN Soccernet | date = 5 October 2008 | accessdate = 2 November 2012}}</ref> During the [[2009\u201310 Serie A|2009\u201310 season]], he managed to play in most games and became somewhat of a fan favourite.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n\n===Milan===\nOn 20 July 2010, it was confirmed on [[A.C. Milan|Milan]]'s website that Papastathopoulos had joined the team, after Genoa and Milan reached an agreement to transfer Papastathopoulos to the club for \u20ac14&nbsp;million, with the following payment schedule: [[Gianmarco Zigoni]] (half of his registration rights, valued at \u20ac3.75&nbsp;million), [[Nnamdi Oduamadi]] (half of his rights, valued at \u20ac3.5&nbsp;million) and [[Rodney Strasser]] (half of his rights, valued at \u20ac2.25&nbsp;million) in a [[Co-ownership (football)|co-ownership deal]], plus \u20ac4.5&nbsp;million in funds.<ref>{{cite web |title=Welcome Sokratis! |url=http://www.acmilan.com/NewsDetail.aspx?idNews=124929 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120724033155/http://www.acmilan.com/NewsDetail.aspx?idNews=124929 |url-status=dead |archive-date=24 July 2012 |publisher=A.C. Milan |date=20 July 2010 |accessdate=20 July 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=1506456.html|title=Milan pick up Genoa starlet Papastathopoulos|date=20 July 2010|accessdate=22 July 2010|publisher=UEFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acmilan.com/uploads/club/bilancio2010/pdf/Bilancio_Gruppo_Milan_10.pdf |title=AC Milan Group 2010 Annual Report |date=April 2011 |accessdate=11 June 2011 |publisher=A.C. Milan |language=Italian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120515220657/http://www.acmilan.com/uploads/club/bilancio2010/pdf/Bilancio_Gruppo_Milan_10.pdf |archivedate=15 May 2012  }}</ref> Papastathopoulos was the club's first arrival under new manager [[Massimiliano Allegri]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=1506456.html|title=Milan pick up Genoa starlet Papastathopoulos|date=20 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n====Genoa return====\nOn 24 May 2011, Milan and Genoa executives [[Adriano Galliani]] and [[Enrico Preziosi]], respectively, formed a verbal agreement to solve the player ownerships (subject to player agreements) of [[Kevin-Prince Boateng]], [[Alberto Paloschi]], [[Marco Amelia]] and [[Giacomo Beretta]]. The deal entailed that Milan bought back Gianmarco Zigoni, Rodney Strasser and Nnamdi Oduamadi (all under original price),<ref name=Genoa2011bilancio/> while Genoa bought back Papastathopoulos for \u20ac13&nbsp;million, which effectively made the ''de facto'' loan cost for Milan \u20ac1&nbsp;million.<ref name=Genoa2011bilancio>{{cite book|title= Genoa CFC SpA Report and Accounts on 31 December 2011  | date =  April 2012|publisher= registroimprese.it/ CCIAA Archive | language = Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.acmilan.com/uploads/club/bilancio2011/ | title = Relazione e Bilancio al 31 Dicembre 2011 | language = Italian | publisher = Ac milan | accessdate = 2 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2011/maggio/25/Boateng_del_Milan_Riscatto_milioni_ga_10_110525107.shtml|title=Boateng e del Milan Riscatto da 7 milioni|date=25 May 2011|accessdate=11 June 2011|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\n===Werder Bremen===\n[[File:Sokratis Papastathopoulos 2012.JPG|thumb|upright|Papastathopoulos with [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] in 2012]]\n\nOn 21 July 2011, Papastathopoulos moved to German club [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on a loan deal until the end of the [[2011\u201312 SV Werder Bremen season|2011\u201312 season]], with the option to purchase outright.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.werder.de/en/aktuell/news/34406.php|title=Sokratis introduced|date=21 July 2011|accessdate=16 January 2013|publisher=SV Werder Bremen|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140518171636/http://www.werder.de/en/aktuell/news/34406.php|archivedate=18 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/11/transfer-zone/2011/07/21/2584535/official-sokratis-papastathopoulos-joins-werder-bremen-on|title=Official: Sokratis Papastathopoulos joins Werder Bremen on loan from Genoa|date=21 July 2011|accessdate=16 January 2013|website=Goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/936169/werder-bremen-swoop-for-papastathopoulos-on-loan-from-genoa?cc=3888|title=Bremen swoop for Papastathopoulos|date=21 July 2011|accessdate=16 January 2013|website=ESPN Soccernet}}</ref> Following impressive performances on loan, on 16 April 2012, it was announced that Papastathopoulos would join Bremen on a permanent basis for a \u20ac5&nbsp;million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/clubfootball/news/newsid=1615865.html|title=Papastathopoulos makes Bremen move permanent|date=16 April 2012|accessdate=16 January 2013|publisher=FIFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/sports/2012/04/16/papastathopoulos-completes-bremen-switch/|title=Papastathopoulos completes Bremen switch|date=16 April 2012|accessdate=16 January 2013|publisher=Fox News Channel}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title= Genoa CFC SpA Report and Accounts on 31 December 2012 |publisher= registroimprese.it/ CCIAA Archive | language = Italian}}</ref> The [[2012\u201313 SV Werder Bremen season|2012\u201313 season]], however, was not a good one for the club. In March 2013, in the midst of a relegation battle and with tensions high, Papastathopoulos engaged in a training ground brawl with teammate [[Marko Arnautovi\u0107]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2013/03/29/werder-bremen-stars-show-strain-of-relegation-battle-with-petulant-training-ground-brawl-3565176/|title=Werder Bremen stars show strain of relegation battle with petulant training ground brawl|date=29 March 2013|newspaper=Metro|location=London}}</ref> Bremen would ultimately finish the year in 14th, staving-off relegation.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\n===Borussia Dortmund===\nOn 24 May 2013, the eve of the [[2013 UEFA Champions League Final|2013 Champions League Final]] between [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and [[Borussia Dortmund]], Papastathopoulos completed a \u20ac9.5&nbsp;million transfer to Dortmund, agreeing to a five-year contract through to 2018.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.bvb.de/?%87%ECY%1B%E7%F4%9C%5Ch%E2%81%99 | title = BVB sign \"Sokratis\" | publisher = Borussia Dortmund | date = 28 May 2013 | accessdate = 28 July 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.sport-fm.gr/article/upegrapse-sti-ntortmoud-o-swkratis/677300 | title = \u03a5\u03c0\u03ad\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c8\u03b5 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039d\u03c4\u03cc\u03c1\u03c4\u03bc\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03c4 \u03bf \u03a3\u03c9\u03ba\u03c1\u03ac\u03c4\u03b7\u03c2! | publisher = sport-fm.gr| date = 23 May 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footballvs.org/sokratis-papastathopoulos-vs-msakni/|title=Sokratis Papastathopoulos vs Msakni \u2013 Football VS \u2013 Real football face to face|accessdate=25 October 2016|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304092701/http://www.footballvs.org/sokratis-papastathopoulos-vs-msakni/|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Upon signing, he spoke about the deal, saying, \"Money did not play a role in my decision to join Dortmund. My own future was all that mattered and I am convinced that I made the right decision.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-au/news/4016/main/2013/06/05/4027048/sokratis-i-did-not-join-dortmund-for-the-money|title=Sokratis: I did not join Dortmund for the money |website=Goal.com | date = 5 June 2013 | accessdate = 28 July 2013 | first = Stefan | last = Coerts}}</ref> With centre-back [[Felipe Santana]] departing Dortmund for [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]], Papastathopoulos began as the effective third-choice behind tandem [[Neven Suboti\u0107]] and [[Mats Hummels]]. Borussia Dortmund Sporting Director [[Michael Zorc]] expressed his satisfaction with the deal: \"We are delighted that Sokratis has decided to join Borussia Dortmund. He is a flexible player capable to play in a variety of positions in defence who we believe has tremendous potential.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/borussia-dortmund/transfer-talk/news/papastathopoulos-joins-dortmund_86480.html|title=Sokratis Papastathopoulos joins Borussia Dortmund | publisher = sportsmole.co.uk| date = 28 May 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 July 2013, Papastathopoulos made his debut for Dortmund in a pre-season friendly away to Swiss club [[FC Basel|Basel]] at [[St. Jakob-Park]], along with fellow BVB debutants [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang]] and [[Henrikh Mkhitaryan]]. On 27 July, he won his first title with the club after entering the match as a substitute in a 4\u20132 win over Bayern Munich for the [[2013 DFL-Supercup|2013]] [[DFL-Supercup]].<ref name=goaldotcom>{{cite news|url=https://www.thefinalball.com/jogo.php?id=2821403|title=DFL SuperCup Final 2013| publisher = footballzz.com}}</ref> On 1 November 2013, he scored his first goal for Dortmund in a 6\u20131 win over [[VfB Stuttgart]] in the [[Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000276334.php|title=Lewandowski shines as Stuttgart hit for six|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105001353/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000276334.php|archivedate=5 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nPapastathopoulos' strong first year with Dortmund was rewarded with his selection to the best XI of the [[2013\u201314 Bundesliga]] campaign. The selection was organised in a worldwide fan vote by the governing body of the Bundesliga through its official website. The description of his play following his nomination was, \"The definition of defense falls on him. The Greek stopper took advantage of the opportunities given to him by the absence of Neven Suboti\u0107 and Mats Hummels. Stable, with leadership characteristics and tendency to win the ball without making easily a mistake.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.protothema.gr/sports/article/374148/stin-kaluteri-11ada-tou-germanikou-protathlimatos-o-sokratis-papastathopoulos/|title=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03ba\u03b1\u03bb\u03cd\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b7 11\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0393\u03b5\u03c1\u03bc\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u03a0\u03c1\u03c9\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03bb\u03ae\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf \u03a3\u03c9\u03ba\u03c1\u03ac\u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2| publisher = protothema.gr | date = 28 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/fanzone/team-of-the-season/|title=Team of the season|publisher=Bundesliga|date=23 April 2014|access-date=28 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140412230941/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/fanzone/team-of-the-season/|archive-date=12 April 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2014, Papastathopoulos was ruled out of action for two weeks with a broken fibula. He suffered the injury to his right leg in Dortmund's 1\u20130 win over [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]], a result that ended a five-match Bundesliga losing streak for the club. After recovering early, he was deemed fit for BVB's [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] match against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 26 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/dortmunds-sokratis-sidelined-two-weeks#:z5zDXxiyWaOC0A |title=Dortmund's Sokratis sidelined for two weeks| publisher = fourfourtwo.com | date = 10 November 2014}}</ref> On 3 January 2015, football news website Goal.com assessed statistics to determine which players maintained the highest tackle success rate in the first half of the 2014\u201315 season across Europe's top five leagues; Papastathopoulos finished joint-third, alongside [[Hamburger SV]]'s [[Matthias Ostrzolek]], having won 92.59 percent of all tackles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1717/editorial/2015/01/03/7608302/who-is-the-best-tackler-in-europe-this-season|title=Who is the best tackler in Europe this season?| website = Goal.com| date = 5 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn the summer of 2015, Papastathopoulos was linked with moves to various English [[Premier League]] clubs as Dortmund prepared for a new start following long-time manager [[J\u00fcrgen Klopp]]'s departure. Dortmund Sporting Director [[Michael Zorc]], however, said Papastathopoulos would still have a part to play for BVB in new manager [[Thomas Tuchel]]'s debut season with the club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://pulse.ng/sports/football/borussia-dortmund-michael-zorc-quells-rumours-over-sokratis-papastathopoulos-and-sven-bender-id3890196.html|title=MIchael Zorc quells rumours over Sokratis Papastathopoulos and Sven Bender| publisher = pulse.ng| date = 21 June 2015}}</ref> On 26 October 2015, Papastathopoulos extended his contract with Borussia Dortmund until 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/725/bundesliga/2015/10/26/16696102/sokratis-extends-dortmund-contract|title=Sokratis Papastathopoulos extends Borussia Dortmund contract |website=Goal.com |date=26 October 2015|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref>\n{{Quote_box|width=30%|align=right|quote=\"The defensive work that Sokratis puts in is just unbelievable.\" |source=German defender [[Mats Hummels]] on Papastathopoulos<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bvb.de/eng/Teams/First-Team/Sokratis |title=Sokratis Papastathopoulos}}</ref>}} After the extension, Zorc said, \"We are very pleased that we have been able to sign with Sokratis, another top performer, on a long term.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/greek-defender-sokratis-extends-contract-with-dortmund-115102700664_1.html |title=Greek defender Sokratis extends contract with Dortmund}}</ref> During Tuchel's tenure, Papastathopoulos was promoted to be partner-in-chief to [[Mats Hummels]] over [[Neven Subotic]].{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n\nOn 19 December 2015, Papastathopoulos scored his first goal in the [[2015\u201316 Bundesliga]] in an eventual 2\u20131 away loss to [[1. FC K\u00f6ln]], giving his club the lead in the first-half from a header from a corner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/blmd17n-1-fc-koeln-2-1-borussia-dortmund-report.jsp|title=BLMD17 \u2013 1. FC K\u00f6ln 2\u20131 Borussia Dortmund \u2013 Report |accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref> On 30 January 2016, in a league game against [[FC Ingolstadt 04|Ingolstadt 04]], Papastathopoulos reached his 100th Bundesliga appearance with Dortmund. On 22 February 2016, Papastathopoulos missed the second leg of the [[UEFA Europa League]] round-of-32 tie against [[FC Porto]] and the Bundesliga clash with [[Bayern Munich]] due to an adductor injury, as tests confirmed that the 27-year-old would be out for up to three weeks. The Greek centre back picked up the injury during Dortmund's 1\u20130 win against [[Bayer Leverkusen]] and was replaced 13 minutes from time at the BayArena.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soccernews.com/injured-sokratis-to-miss-key-dortmund-clashes/194061/|title=Injured Sokratis to miss key Dortmund clashes \u2013 Soccer News|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/bundesliga/news/detail/item130089/papastathopoulos-to-miss-crucial-bvb-ties/|title=Papastathopoulos to miss crucial BVB ties \u2013 Fox Sports|date=23 February 2016|accessdate=25 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409002015/http://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/bundesliga/news/detail/item130089/papastathopoulos-to-miss-crucial-bvb-ties/|archive-date=9 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 21 May 2016, Papastathopoulos featured in his third [[DFB-Pokal]] final in a row, putting in a tremendous performance despite a missed penalty, but he did not succeed in winning the DFB-Pokal for first time in his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/Germany/ntamplouxos-sta-penalti-h-mpagern.4071385.html|title=\u039d\u03c4\u03b1\u03bc\u03c0\u03bb\u03bf\u03cd\u03c7\u03bf\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c0\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1\u03bb\u03c4\u03b9 \u03b7 \u039c\u03c0\u03ac\u03b3\u03b5\u03c1\u03bd|publisher=sport24.gr|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe started the [[2016-17 Bundesliga|2016\u201317 season]] as the undisputed leader in BVB defence. On 15 September 2016, he netted the second goal in an away crashing 6\u20130 against [[Legia Warsaw]] on a Group [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] match.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2017/matches/round=2000783/match=2019293/postmatch/report/index.html?rss=2400199%20Dortmund%20six-shooters%20wreck%20Legia's%20comeback|title=UEFA Champions League \u2013 Legia-Dortmund \u2013 Dortmund six-shooters wreck Legia's comeback \u2013 UEFA|last=UEFA.com|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref> On 4 January 2017 the German magazine ''\"Kicker\"'' listed the Greek international as one of the best players in the German [[Bundesliga]]. The magazine paid a tribute to the best players currently playing in the German Bundesliga, separating them out into different categories. In the first category (World Class) no defenders were listed, however, Papastathopoulos was one of three defenders listed in the second category, International Class. The other two defenders included [[Mats Hummels]] of Bayern Munich and [[Jonathan Tah]] of Bayer Leverkusen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/EllinesExoterikou/nea-diakrish-gia-papastathopoylo.4462277.html |title=\u039d\u03ad\u03b1 \u03b4\u03b9\u03ac\u03ba\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf  |publisher=sport24.gr |accessdate=4 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Sokratis170727.jpg|thumb|right|Papastathopoulos (right) training with [[Borussia Dortmund]] in 2017]]\n\nOn 8 February 2017, in a [[DFB Pokal]] home win on penalties' game against [[Hertha BSC|Hertha Berlin]], Papastathopoulos' two quickfire (in a minute) bookings for dissent saw Dortmund finish extra time with 10 men before [[Fabian Lustenberger]], [[Vladimir Darida]] and [[Salomon Kalou]] all erred from the spot, rendering [[Christian Pulisic]]'s miss irrelevant.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/german-dfb-pokal/story/3056496/borussia-dortmund-reach-pokal-quarters-after-shootout-with-hertha-schalke-win |title=Dortmund reach Pokal quarters after shootout with Hertha; Schalke win |website=ESPN FC |accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> On 25 February 2017, Dortmund made three changes from last weekend's 3\u20130 win over [[VfL Wolfsburg]] and it was two of those, Papastathopoulos and [[Raphael Guerreiro]], who combined to open the scoring in the 13th minute in a 3\u20130 away win against [[SC Freiburg]]. Papastathopoulos looked to be offside as Guerreiro swung in a free-kick from the right, which the Greece defender met with a header planted inside the right-hand post.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.gr/football/article/1051478/kollise-o-sokratis-vid |title=\u03a4\u03bf \u03ba\u03cc\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03bf \u03a3\u03c9\u03ba\u03c1\u03ac\u03c4\u03b7\u03c2  |publisher=gazzetta.gr |accessdate=25 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/spieltag/1-bundesliga/2016-17/22/3317450/spielbericht_sc-freiburg-7_borussia-dortmund-17.html |title=Freiburg vs Dortmund 0\u20133  |publisher=kicker.de |accessdate=25 February 2017}}</ref>\nOn 16 April 2017, Papastathopoulos was the one who had a quick reaction to an [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] equalising, by scoring a goal after [[Sven Bender]]'s assist giving a lead to the score in his team in a final 3\u20131 home win.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/spieltag/1-bundesliga/2016-17/29/3317506/spielbericht_borussia-dortmund-17_eintracht-frankfurt-32.html |title=Dortmund vs Eintracht 3\u20131  |publisher=kicker.de |accessdate=16 April 2017}}</ref>\nOn 26 April 2017, helped Borussia Dortmund to a 3\u20132 win over [[Bayern Munich]] and their fourth consecutive [[DFB-Pokal]] final. On 20 May 2017, Papastathopoulos reached 100 appearances with Dortmund in [[Bundesliga]] in a home game against [[SV Werder Bremen]] and secured automatic qualification to the group stage of next season's [[UEFA Champions League]]. On 27 May 2017, in his fourth [[DFB-Pokal]] final in a row, Borussia Dortmund claimed a first DFB-Pokal win since 2012 as [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang]]'s penalty defeated [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fearthewall.com/2017/5/27/15705332/dfb-pokal-match-report-dortmund-wins-a-title |title=DFB Pokal Match Report: Dortmund wins a title |publisher=fearthewall.com |accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tagesschau.de/sport/dortmund-pokalsieger-101.html |title=Borussia Dortmund gewinnt DFB-Pokal |publisher=tagesschau.de |accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 August 2017, as the captain of the club, he lost the [[2017 DFL-Supercup]] on penalties' game against [[Bayern Munich]]. On 17 September 2017, he scored at the end of the first half against [[1. FC K\u00f6ln]], giving a lead of two goals in his club. It was his first goal for the [[2017-18 Bundesliga|2017\u201318 season]] and was secured with the use of VAR (Video Assistant Referee) method.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/EllinesExoterikou/gkol-toy-papastathopoyloy-kontra-sthn-kolwnia-me-xrhsh-toy-var.4850517.html |title=\u0393\u03ba\u03bf\u03bb \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5 \u03ba\u03cc\u03bd\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03bf\u03bb\u03c9\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c7\u03c1\u03ae\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 VAR! |publisher=sport24.gr |accessdate=17 September 2017}}</ref> On 14 October 2017, Borussia Dortmund's unbeaten start to the season was ended by [[RB Leipzig]]'s 3\u20132 away win, as the Greek defender initially in trying to push the ball away helped Leipzig winger [[Yussuf Poulsen]] to score, while at the beginning of second half, was sent off for a foul in the box and [[Jean-Kevin Augustin]] scored the penalty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contra.gr/Columns/contra-epithesi/dortmund/me-gkafa-papastathopoyloy-anatroph-h-leipsia.4891149.html |title=\u039c\u03b5 \u03b3\u03ba\u03ac\u03c6\u03b1 \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c0\u03ae \u03b7 \u039b\u03b5\u03b9\u03c8\u03af\u03b1 |publisher=contra.gr |accessdate=14 October 2017}}</ref> On 17 October 2017, after losing its [[UEFA Champions League]] opening games in Group H to [[Tottenham]] and [[Real Madrid]], Dortmund needed a win to kick-start its campaign in Europe's premier club competition, but they succeeded only to seal an away draw against Cypriot champions [[APOEL]], as the Greek defender equalised with a header to [[Mario G\u00f6tze]]'s cross.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/8/main/2017/10/17/39500952/apoel-1-borussia-dortmund-1-sokratis-header-spares-burkis |title=APOEL vs Borussia Dortmund 1\u20131 |website=Goal.com |accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/17/champions-league-roundup-apoel-borussia-dortmund-draw |title=Champions League roundup: Borussia Dortmund held to draw by Apoel |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref> On 4 November 2017, in the derby against rivals [[Bayern Munich]] he suffered a leg injury, during the first half, and was substituted by [[Jeremy Toljan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/ellada/ethniki_elladas/traymatisthke-o-papastathopoylos-agwnia-gia-thn-ethnikh-elladas.4922818.html |title=\u03a4\u03c1\u03b1\u03c5\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03ba\u03b5 \u03bf \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2, \u03b1\u03b3\u03c9\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2 |publisher=sport24.gr |accessdate=4 November 2017}}</ref> and two weeks later in an away game against [[VfB Stuttgart]] has received a heavy blow and replaced at the end of the first half from [[Dan-Axel Zagadou]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dw.com/en/as-it-happened-stuttgart-2-1-borussia-dortmund/a-41430252 |title=As it happened: Stuttgart 2\u20131 Borussia Dortmund |publisher=dw.com |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Arsenal===\nOn 2 July 2018, [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] announced that Papastathopoulos has agreed a long-term contract with the club for a reported fee \u00a317.6&nbsp;million and will wear the number 5 shirt.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/sokratis-papastathopoulos-signs|title=Sokratis Papastathopoulos signs}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2778354-sokratis-papastathopoulos-completes-arsenal-transfer-for-reported-176m-fee|title=Sokratis Papastathopoulos Completes Arsenal Transfer for Reported \u00a317.6M Fee}}</ref> On 12 August 2018, he made his official debut with the club as a starter, at [[Emirates Stadium|Emirates]] in a 2\u20130 loss against champions [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. On 4 October 2018, Papastathopoulos scored his first for the club, setting the Gunners on their way to a comfortable 3\u20130 victory over [[Qarabag]] in the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Europa League]] group stage. After just four minutes of play in Baku, the centre-back was left unmarked inside the opposing penalty area, deflecting the ball home after the initial header fell into his path.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/qarabag-vs-arsenal/401956|title=Qarabag FK 0\u20133 Arsenal: Trio score first goals as Gunners cruise in Azerbaijan}}</ref> Papastathopoulos, was named to the UEFA Europa League Team of the Week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=2573295.html |title=Who makes our Europa League Team of the Week?}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 October 2018, Papastathopoulos was forced off during Greece's 2\u20130 defeat to [[Finland national football team|Finland]] and was believed to have sprained his ankle. Papastathopoulos was at the heart of Unai Emery's defence since the Spaniard took over the reins in the summer and a fixture in a winning run of nine matches.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11670/11527476/arsenal-defender-sokratis-injured-on-international-duty |title=Arsenal defender Sokratis injured on international duty}}</ref> On 21 February 2019, he netted his second goal as an Arsenal player, taking advantage of a missed punch from [[BATE Borisov]]'s goalie [[Denis Scherbitskiy]] to head the ball into an empty net following a corner kick from [[Granit Xhaka]]. The goal sealed a 3\u20130 home win for Arsenal, sending them through to the round of 32 in the [[2018-19 UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47303991 |title=Arsenal vs BATE Borisov 3\u20130}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 April 2019, Papastathopoulos was named to the [[UEFA Europa League]]\u2019s \u2018Team of the week\u2019, a second time during the season, after playing a vital role in Arsenal's 2\u20130 win over [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]] in the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#QF 1.1|first leg of the quarter-finals]]. Papastathopoulos was one of four Arsenal players selected in the Europa League \u2018Team of the week\u2019 along with [[Petr \u010cech]], [[Ainsley Maitland-Niles]], and [[Aaron Ramsey]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/performancezone/teamoftheweek/ |title=Who makes our Europa League Team of the Week?}}</ref> On 24 April 2019, Papastathopoulos scored his maiden goal in the English [[Premier League]] rose highest to connect with a corner from the right wing, masterfully heading the ball into the net from point blank range, but Arsenal slipped to a 1\u20133 defeat against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47505642 |title=Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Arsenal 3\u20131}}</ref> On 29 May 2019, he started in the [[2019 UEFA Europa League Final]] against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in which Arsenal lost 4\u20131. This was the first time Arsenal had conceded four goals in a European match since a 5\u20131 loss to Bayern Munich in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48368406 |title=Chelsea vs Arsenal 4\u20131}}</ref> On 27 October 2019, Papastathopoulos\u2014marking his 50th appearance\u2014scored his first goal in the season, after [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] failed to clear [[Nicolas P\u00e9p\u00e9]]'s corner in a 2\u20132 home draw game.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50113576 |title= Arsenal vs Crystal Palace 2\u20132}}</ref> On 1 January 2020, Papastathopoulos smashed home a close-range finish to seal a 2\u20130 win over [[Manchester United]], securing [[Mikel Arteta]] his first victory in charge of the Gunners. He was named Man of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/arsenal-vs-man-utd/408181 |title=Arsenal 2-0 Manchester United: Gunners claim first win under Mikel Arteta}}</ref> On 2 March 2020, [[Reiss Nelson]]'s assist finished clinically from the Greek international , whose clipped volley into the corner, to give the lead in a 2-0 away win against [[Portsmouth F.C.]], helping Arsenal to be the first team in the [[FA Cup]] quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51697793 |title= Portsmouth vs Arsenal 0\u20132}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:20130814 AT-GR Sokratis Papastathopoulos 2368.jpg|thumb|upright|Papastathopoulos playing for [[Greece national football team|Greece]] in 2013]]\n\nPapastathopoulos was called up for the [[Greece national football team|Greek senior team]] on 1 February 2008<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/competitions/euro/news/kind=1/newsid=652323.html |title=Greece Squad call up |publisher=UEFA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080202071137/http://www.uefa.com/competitions/euro/news/kind%3D1/newsid%3D652323.html |archivedate=2 February 2008  }}</ref> and made his debut on 5 February 2008 in the 1\u20130 friendly victory against the [[Czech national football team|Czech Republic]]. The Greece squad for [[UEFA Euro 2008]] was announced by [[Otto Rehhagel]] on 27 May 2008, and Papastathopoulos was the unfortunate player to be cut from the provisional squad of 24 to the final 23-man selection.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=702185.html | title = Greece's Papastathopoulos drops out | publisher = UEFA | date = 28 May 2008 | accessdate = 2 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nPapastathopoulos became the first player to be sent off at [[UEFA Euro 2012]] during the opening game of the tournament against co-hosts [[Poland national football team|Poland]] after receiving two yellow cards, following what pundits decried as two poor decisions by referee [[Carlos Velasco Carballo]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Glendenning|first=Barry|title=Euro 2012: Poland 1\u20131 Greece \u2013 as it happened|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2012/jun/08/euro-2012-poland-greece-live|accessdate=9 June 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|date=8 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, Papastathopoulos was named to Greece's squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/greece/10810255/Greece-World-Cup-2014-squad.html|title=Greece World Cup 2014 squad|date=2 June 2014|accessdate=30 June 2014|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London}}</ref> He started in each of the team's group matches, helping them to a [[clean sheet]] against [[Japan national football team|Japan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25285183|title=Japan 0\u20130 Greece|date=20 June 2014|accessdate=30 June 2014|work=BBC Sport}}</ref> In the [[2014 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]], Papastathopoulos scored his first international goal, equalising in second half stoppage time against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]]. However, the Greeks were eventually defeated 5\u20133 in a [[penalty shootout]] by the [[2013 Copa Centroamericana|Central American champions]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/27961189|title=Costa Rica 1\u20131 Greece|accessdate=30 June 2014|date=29 June 2014|work=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 June 2019, following the loss to [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]] at the [[Olympic Stadium]], Papastathopoulos called for immediate changes to be made to the Greek national team set-up, and he allegedly requested for [[Angelos Anastasiadis]] to be removed from his role of head coach when speaking to EPO president, Evangelos Grammenos.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sportdog.gr/sports/podosfairo/article/524244/tsoynami-sthn-ethnikh-aytoi-feygoyn-mazi-me-swkrath-apanthsh-fwtia-ton-diwxnei-o-aggelos |title=\"\u03a4\u03c3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03bc\u03b9\" \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u2013 \u0391\u03c5\u03c4\u03bf\u03af \u03c6\u03b5\u03cd\u03b3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03bc\u03b1\u03b6\u03af \u03bc\u03b5 \u03a3\u03c9\u03ba\u03c1\u03ac\u03c4\u03b7 \u2013 \u0391\u03c0\u03ac\u03bd\u03c4\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7-\u03c6\u03c9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ac \u2013 \u03a4\u03bf\u03bd \"\u03b4\u03b9\u03ce\u03c7\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9\" \u03bf \u0386\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2! |accessdate=11 June 2019|date=12 June 2019|publisher=sportdog.gr}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/athlitismos/44287_mpahalo-i-ethniki-aihmes-papastathopoyloy-apantisi-anastasiadi-vids |title=\u039c\u03c0\u03ac\u03c7\u03b1\u03bb\u03bf \u03b7 \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae! \u0391\u03b9\u03c7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c2 \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5, \u03b1\u03c0\u03ac\u03bd\u03c4\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03b9\u03ac\u03b4\u03b7  |accessdate=12 June 2019|date=12 June 2019|publisher=ethnos.gr}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 7 March 2020}}<ref name=\"SW\">{{Soccerway |id=19278 |accessdate=30 September 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|Domestic<br>League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Domestic<br>Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<br>Competition<sup>1</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<br>Tournaments<sup>2</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|[[2005\u201306 Alpha Ethniki|2005\u201306]]\n|0||0||2||1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||2||1\n|-\n|[[Niki Volou FC|Niki Volou]] (loan)\n|[[2005\u201306 Beta Ethniki|2005\u201306]]\n|11||0||0 <!-- Niki Volou played only two cup games during the time Papastathopoulos was with them, coindidentally against AEK, but he was not fielded; see match reports at http://www.aek.com/history/showMatch.php?match_ID=301&details_ID=290 and http://www.aek.com/history/showMatch.php?match_ID=315&details_ID=304 -->||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||11||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[A